'policy of lying in court when denying detainees claims that they weretortured in the course of interrogation.  The Landau commission soughtto correct this problem by legalizing a list of torture methods --thus eliminating the fear that a detainee might be released if thosemethods were used to extract a confession.  The fact that the need tolie still persists would seem to indicate that SHABAK is not stickingto the "approved" torture methods. -- Yigal]--Yigal ArensUSC/ISI                                                TV made me do it!arens@isi.edu
